# Keep the prod image built from a clean seed, not the local dev working
# tree. `Dockerfile` does `COPY brain-repo/ /brain/`, which — without this
# file — would also copy local swamp runtime state (SQLite DBs, cached
# evaluated workflows, etc.) that must never ship in the image; runtime
# state is regenerated in-container / hydrated from R2 instead (see
# `hydrateRepo` in src/runtime/brain.ts).
brain-repo/.swamp/

# Never needed inside the container image; the base image installs its own
# tooling and node_modules is host-platform-specific dev tooling for the
# Worker itself, not the sandboxed brain-repo seed.
node_modules/

# Local wrangler dev state — never relevant to the container image.
.wrangler/
